1. Definitions
In this Agreement:
(a) "child" or "children" means "names and dates of birth of children involved";
(b) "cohabit" means to live with another person in a relationship resembling marriage;
(c) "company" means [name of company] (if one of the parties owns a company);
(d) "cottage" means the property at [street address] in [city], [PROVINCE];
(e) "CRA" means Canada Revenue Agency;
(f) "equalization payment" means the payment referred to in the [INSERT PROVINCIAL LEGISLATION NAME HERE for property division];
(g) "MAINTENANCE ENFORCEMENT AGENCY" means the MAINTENANCE ENFORCEMENT AGENCY NAME described in the [Insert Provincial Legislation name here Act], or any successor support enforcement agency;
(h) "Guidelines" means the Federal Child Support Guidelines, as defined in s. 2(1) of the Divorce Act, or, in the case of unmarried parents or spouses, "Guidelines" means the Child Support Guidelines as defined in s. 1(1) of the [INSERT PROVINCIAL LEGISLATION NAME HERE];
(i) "Indexing factor" means the percentage change for a given month in the Consumer Price Index for [Canada] for prices of All-Items (as published by Statistics Canada) the same month of the previous year;
(j) "matrimonial home" means the property at [street address] in [city], [Province];
(k) "net family property" means net family property as defined in the [INSERT PROVINCIAL LEGISLATION NAME HERE];
(l) "property" means property as defined in the [INSERT PROVINCIAL LEGISLATION NAME HERE]; and
(m) "section 7 expenses" means the special or extraordinary expenses referred to in s.7 of the Guidelines.
